{
  "doc_id": "52697",
  "text": "Previously, we reported that M-CSF promotes monocyte survival through the activation of the PI3-K/AKT pathway [CITATION_1] . In addition to AKT activation, M-CSF stimulates PKC in human monocytes and increases NF-kB DNA binding [CITATION_2] . However, whether PKC and/or NF-kB activation is critical in M-CSFstimulated mononuclear phagocyte survival and/or differentiation is unclear. In other cells, PKC plays an important role in NF-kB activation and cell survival [CITATION_3] , however the specific mechanisms of this activation and the biological effects on cellular phenotype are not known. Therefore, we focused at understanding the role of PKC in the regulation of NF-kB activation and M-CSF-induced monocyte survival.",
